Design Brief: FonixFlow Tracker Setup — Compact UE5 Editor Panel

CONTEXT
This is a panel inside the Unreal Engine 5 editor (dockable, ~350 px wide,
variable height). It is built in C++ Slate and must follow Unreal's dark
editor aesthetic. The user is a camera operator or technician setting up a
physical lens tracker in a studio. They open the panel once per shoot day,
run through it top to bottom, then close it. Speed and clarity matter more
than discoverability.

CURRENT PROBLEMS
- 8 vertical sections separated by horizontal rules, all stacked in a scrollbox
- Every section has a bold 12pt section title + a 10pt grey description
  sentence below it + the actual controls — this triples the height of every row
- Lens type selection (Prime / Zoom) renders as two large card-style radio
  buttons each with a title + description sub-line, taking ~160 px for a
  binary choice
- Protocol selection repeats the same card pattern for a choice that will be
  FreeD 99% of the time
- The Network section shows "Your IP" in a full bordered card + a separate
  port line + an instruction paragraph
- The calibration section has a LiveLink readout box, a focus box (Near/Far),
  an optional zoom box (Wide/Tele), and an Apply button — all in separate borders
- The log at the bottom is a free-height monospace text block inside another
  scrollbox

DESIGN GOALS
1. Everything above the action buttons fits in ~500 px with no scrolling on
   a 1080p monitor (panel is typically docked to ~350 px wide)
2. Section titles replaced by compact inline ALL-CAPS labels — like a
   property row in the Details panel — not large bold headings
3. Lens Type and Protocol: single horizontal row of labelled radio/toggle
   chips — not card blocks
4. Network: show IP + port in one single-line row, right-aligned Refresh button
5. Calibration live readout: Focus (cm) and Zoom (mm) side-by-side in one
   row, small monospace numbers, green/blue tinted
6. Focus capture: Near and Far on one row each — current value left,
   button right — two rows total
7. Zoom capture (zoom lens only): same pattern as focus — Wide / Tele,
   two rows
8. SETUP NOW and APPLY CALIBRATION stay as full-width prominent buttons
   (height ~36 px), slightly accent-coloured
9. Status and Log collapse into a small toggle-able accordion at the bottom
   labelled "Log v" — closed by default, only ~24 px tall when closed.
   When open, shows ~100 px of monospace log text

VISUAL STYLE
- Follow Unreal Editor dark theme:
    background    #1a1a1a
    panel border  #2a2a2a
    text          #cccccc
    muted text    #666666
- Accent for live data:
    focus value   #33cc66  (green)
    zoom value    #66aaff  (blue)
- Accent for action buttons:
    Setup Now     #2a4a6a  (steel blue tint)
    Apply Calib   #1a5a2a  (dark green tint)
- Captured / confirmed values:  bright white  #ffffff
- Uncaptured / pending values:  amber         #cc8833
- Typography (Unreal editor defaults):
    section labels  Regular 10pt ALL-CAPS
    input labels    Regular 10pt
    live values     Bold 11pt Mono
    log text        Mono 9pt
- No icons needed — text labels only

